The most notable achievement of the United States under the Articles of Confederation was:

\boxed{F}

The Northwest Ordinance of 1787, enacted under the Articles, established a system for governing and eventually admitting new states from the Northwest Territory, ensuring orderly expansion and benefiting the nation as a whole. This was a significant accomplishment in land policy and territorial organization. Other options either were not part of the Articles or were later addressed by the Constitution.
